# Demo Component Rules

Files in `components/demo/**` mirror the structure of `components/ui/**`. Each
demo file exports one or more variants for the matching UI component.

## Required structure

```jsx
// components/demo/magic/special-effects/border-beam.jsx
import { BorderBeam } from "@/components/ui"

export function BorderBeamDemo() {
  return (/* canonical demo from magicui.design */)
}

export function BorderBeamDemoStart() {
  return (/* minimal example */)
}

export function BorderBeamDemoComponent() {
  return (/* additional variant */)
}
```

## Rules

1. **One file per UI component**, all variants live in that file.
2. **Variant names** start with `<ComponentName>Demo` and PascalCase suffixes.
   See `naming.mdc`.
3. **Imports** come from `@/components/ui` (top-level barrel) — never reach
   into private files like `@/components/ui/button/button.jsx`.
4. **No business logic** — demos are visual examples. Keep helpers, fixture
   data, icons, etc. inline in the file.
5. **No async/data loading** — demos must render instantly without fetch.
6. **`"use client"` only when needed** — only when you import a client-only
   library (motion, cmdk, etc.) or use hooks.
7. **Self-contained** — a demo file should be copyable into another project
   (after fixing the `@/components/ui` import path).

## Variant tab layout

Each `<ShowcaseVariant>` on the page must reference an `exportName` from this
file. If you add a variant here, also add it to the page in `app/demo/...`.
